Zadn

Obrzek 1: Reologick model

Reologick model na obrzku vznikl sriovm zapojenm pruiny a Kelvinova lnku a je charakterizovn parametry:

$$ E_0 = (50 + 10a) \, \mathrm{GPa}, \tag{1.0} \label{eq:E_0} $$

$$ E_1 = (40 + 10b) \, \mathrm{GPa}, \tag{2.0} \label{eq:E_1} $$

$$ \eta_1 = (800 + 100c) \, \mathrm{GPa \cdot s}. \tag{2.1} \label{eq:eta_1} $$

Tyto parametry se v ase nemn, jde tedy o model viskoelastickho materilu bez strnut.

  1. Odvote funkci poddajnosti $J_0(t)$ a sestrojte jej graf. Pro kontrolu budete potebovat hodnoty funkce poddajnosti v asech $t = 0, 10, 20$ a $30 \, \mathrm{s}$ a jej limitn hodnotu pro as rostouc nade vechny meze.

  2. Odvote relaxan funkci $R_0(t)$ a sestrojte jej graf. Pro kontrolu budete potebovat hodnoty funkce poddajnosti v asech $t = 0, 10, 20$ a $30 \, \mathrm{s}$ a jej limitn hodnotu pro as rostouc nade vechny meze.

  3. Zjistte, zda vztah $R_0(t)$ = $1 / J_0(t)$ plat pro libovoln $t \geq 0$, nebo jen pro nkter hodnoty $t$, nebo pro vbec dn.

  4. Popite vvoj deformace odpovdajc napt rostoucmu konstantn rychlost z nulov hodnoty v ase $0$ do hodnoty $8 \, \mathrm{MPa}$ v ase $t_1$. Pitom uvaujte ti rzn ppady: a) $t_1 = 10 \, \mathrm{s}$, b) $t_1 = 20 \, \mathrm{s}$, c) $t_1 = 40 \, \mathrm{s}$. Pro kad z tchto ppad vyneste graf znzorujc vvoj deformace v ase a pracovn diagram znzorujc zvislost mezi naptm a deformac. Vechny ti pracovn diagramy vyneste do stejnho obrzku a nakreslete do nj tak, jak by pracovn diagram vypadal pro extrmn pomal a extrmn rychl zatovn. Pro kontrolu budete potebovat pro ppady a)-c) hodnoty deformace odpovdajc napt $2 \, \mathrm{MPa}, 4 \, \mathrm{MPa}, 6 \, \mathrm{MPa}$ a $8 \, \mathrm{MPa}.$

Napt v elastickm lnku (pruin) je v ppad linernho modelu popsno Hookeovm zkonem

$$ \sigma_{i,e}(t) = E_i \varepsilon_{i,e}(t), \ i=0,1, \tag{3.0} \label{eq:sigma_pruzina}$$

pro linern vazk tlumi je penen napt mrn rychlosti pomrn deformace

$$ \sigma_{1,v}(t) = \eta_1 \dot{\varepsilon}_{1,v}(t). \tag{3.1} \label{eq:sigma_tlumic} $$

Pi paralelnm zapojen pruiny a tlumie, kter oznaujeme jako Kelvinv nek, jsou oba lnky podrobeny stejn deformaci a celkov napt je soutem pspvk prunho a vazkho lnku. Formln to lze popsat vztahy

$$ \varepsilon_1(t) = \varepsilon_{1,e}(t) = \varepsilon_{1,v}(t), \tag{4.0} \label{eq:epsilon_kelvin} $$ $$ \sigma_1(t) = \sigma_{1,e}(t) + \sigma_{1,v}(t). \tag{4.1} \label{eq:sigma_kelvin} $$

Poynting-Thompson model na obr. 1 je sloen z jedn pruiny a jednoho Kelvinova lnku. Vzhledem k sriovmu zapojen jednotek je celkov pomrn deformace

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \varepsilon_0(t) + \varepsilon_1(t). \tag{5.0} \label{eq:epsilon} $$

Je zejm, e kad jednotka pen stejn celkov napt $\sigma(t)$. Podmnky rovnovhy lze zapsat pro kadou jednotku zvl ve tvaru

$$ \sigma(t) = \sigma_{0,e}(t), \tag{6.0} \label{eq:sigma_0} $$ $$ \sigma(t) = \sigma_{1,e}(t) + \sigma_{1,v}(t). \tag{6.1} \label{eq:sigma_1} $$

Po dosazen vztah \eqref{eq:sigma_pruzina} a \eqref{eq:sigma_tlumic} do vztahu \eqref{eq:sigma_0} a \eqref{eq:sigma_1} dostaneme soustavu dvou navzjem nezvislch rovnic

$$ \sigma(t) = E_0 \varepsilon_{0,e}(t) \tag{7.0} \label{eq:sigma_0_dosazena}$$ $$ \sigma(t) = E_{1}\varepsilon_{1,e}(t) + \eta_{1} \dot{\varepsilon}_{1,v}(t). \tag{7.1} \label{eq:sigma_1_dosazena}$$

Ve vztahu \eqref{eq:sigma_0_dosazena} nen nutn pst doln index $e$, protoe v pruin dochz pouze k elastick deformaci $$ \sigma(t) = E_0 \varepsilon_{0}(t), \tag{8.0} \label{eq:sigma_0_dosazena_zjednodusena}$$

vztah \eqref{eq:sigma_1_dosazena} lze na zklad vztahu \eqref{eq:epsilon_kelvin} zjednoduit na

$$ \sigma(t) = E_{1}\varepsilon_{1}(t) + \eta_{1} \dot{\varepsilon}_{1}(t). \tag{8.1} \label{eq:sigma_1_dosazena_zjednodusena}$$

Derivaci vrazu \eqref{eq:sigma_0_dosazena_zjednodusena} podle asu lze zapsat jako

$$ \dot{\sigma}(t) = E_0 \dot{\varepsilon}_{0}(t). \tag{9.0} \label{eq:dsigma}$$

Vyjdenm $\varepsilon_1(t)$ ze vztahu \eqref{eq:epsilon} dostaneme

$$ \varepsilon_1(t) = \varepsilon(t) - \varepsilon_0(t), \tag{10.0} \label{eq:epsilon_1}$$

stejn vztah plat pro derivaci

$$ \dot{\varepsilon}_1(t) = \dot{\varepsilon}(t) - \dot{\varepsilon}_0(t). \tag{11.0} \label{eq:depsilon_1}$$

Dosazenm vraz \eqref{eq:epsilon_1} a \eqref{eq:depsilon_1} do rovnice \eqref{eq:sigma_1_dosazena_zjednodusena} dostaneme

$$ \sigma(t) = E_{1}(\varepsilon(t) - \varepsilon_0(t)) + \eta_{1} (\dot{\varepsilon}(t) - \dot{\varepsilon}_0(t)). \tag{12.0} \label{eq:sigma_1_nevimuz}$$

Rovnici lze dle upravit dosazenm za $\varepsilon_0(t)$ z rovnice \eqref{eq:sigma_0_dosazena_zjednodusena} a za $\dot{\varepsilon}_0(t)$ ze vztahu \eqref{eq:dsigma}

$$ \sigma(t) = E_1 \left( \varepsilon(t) - \frac{\sigma(t)}{E_0} \right) + \eta_1 \left( \dot{\varepsilon}(t) - \frac{\dot{\sigma}(t)}{E_0} \right). \tag {13.0} \label{eq:sigma_dosazeno} $$

Roznsobenm zvorek a pravami dostaneme vztah

$$ E_1 \varepsilon(t) + \eta_1 \dot{\varepsilon}(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0} \sigma(t) + \frac{\eta_1}{E_0} \dot{\sigma}(t) \tag {14.0} \label{eq:dif_rce} $$

Odvozen funkce poddajnosti

Model zatme od asu $t=0\,\mathrm{s}$ konstantnm naptm $\sigma(t) = \hat\sigma H(t)$, kde $H(t)$ je Heavisideova funkce dan pedpisem

$$H(t) = \left\{ \begin{matrix} 0 \quad & \mathrm{pro} \ t < 0, \\ 1 \quad & \mathrm{pro} \ t \geq 0. \end{matrix} \right. \tag{15.0} \label{eq:Heaviside} $$

Protoe $\hat{\sigma} H(t)$ je konstantn funkce, pro jej derivaci plat

$$ \hat{\sigma} \dot{H}(t) = 0. \tag{16.0} \label{eq:derivace_sigma_se_striskou} $$

Dosazenm do vztahu \eqref{eq:dif_rce} dostaneme

$$ E_1 \varepsilon(t) + \eta_1 \dot{\varepsilon}(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0} \hat{\sigma}H(t). \tag {17.0} \label{eq:dif_rce_1} $$

Rovnice \eqref{eq:dif_rce_1} je nehomogenn linern diferenciln rovnice 1. du s konstantnmi koeficienty.

Postup een linern diferenciln rovnice 1. du se skld ze dvou krok:

  1. een pslun homogenn rovnice: Pslunou homogenn linern rovnici lze vyeit separac promnnch. V jejm een se vyskytuje konstanta, oznaen $C$.
  2. Metoda variace konstanty: Konstantu $C$ v een pslun homogenn rovnice z kroku 1 povaujeme za funkci promnn $t$, tj. $$C = C(t)$$ a toto een (s $C(t)$ msto $C$ dosadme do pvodn nehomogenn rovnice. Vznikne rovnice s jednou neznmou a to $C'=C'(t)$. Urme $C'=C'(t)$ a integrac vypotme $C=C(t)$. Po dosazen za $C=C(t)$ dostaneme vsledn een.

Rovnici \eqref{eq:dif_rce_1} pevedeme na tvar

$$ \dot{\varepsilon}(t) + \frac{E_1}{\eta_1} \varepsilon(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t). \tag {18.0} \label{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce} $$

een \eqref{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce} budeme hledat ve tvaru

$$ \varepsilon(t) = C(t) \varepsilon_h(t), \tag{19.0} \label{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni}$$

kde $C(t)$ je hledan funkce promnn $t$ a $\varepsilon_h(t)$ je een homogenn rovnice

$$ \dot{\varepsilon}(t) + \frac{E_1}{\eta_1} \varepsilon(t) = 0. \tag {20.0} \label{eq:homogenni_dif_rce} $$

Funkci $\varepsilon_{h}(t)$ budeme hledat ve tvaru

$$ \varepsilon_{h}(t) = C \exp{(\lambda t)}, \tag{21.0} \label{eq:tvar_reseni_epsilon}$$

kde $C$ a $\lambda$ jsou zatm neuren konstanty.

Derivaci rovnice \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_epsilon} lze zapsat jako

$$ \dot{\varepsilon}_{h}(t) = C \lambda \exp{(\lambda t)}. \tag{22.0} \label{eq:tvar_reseni_depsilon}$$

Dosazen vztah \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_epsilon} a \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_depsilon} do \eqref{eq:homogenni_dif_rce} dostaneme

$$ C \lambda \exp{(\lambda t)} + \frac{E_1}{\eta_{1}} C \exp{(\lambda t)} = 0. \tag{23.0} \label{eq:dosazeni_homo_rce} $$

pravou vztahu \eqref{eq:dosazeni_homo_rce} lze pejt ke tvaru

$$ C \exp{(\lambda t)} \left( \lambda + \frac{E_1}{\eta_1} \right) = 0, \tag{24.0} \label{eq:homo_rce_uprava}$$

kter je splnn prv tehdy, kdy plat

$$ \lambda + \frac{E_1}{\eta_1} = 0. \tag{25.0} \label{eq:charakteristicka_rovnice} $$

Z tto charakteristick rovnice lze vypotat konstantu

$$ \lambda = - \frac{E_1}{\eta_1} \tag{26.0} \label{eq:lambda}. $$

Homogenn een m tedy tvar

$$ \varepsilon_{h}(t) = C \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}, \tag{27.0} \label{eq:reseni_homo}$$

Polome $C=C(t)$ a dosadme do rovnice \eqref{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni}

$$ \varepsilon(t) = C(t) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}, \tag{28.0} \label{eq:28}$$

zderivovnm vrazu dostaneme vztah

$$ \dot{\varepsilon}(t) = \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} - C(t)\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}\exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{29.0} \label{eq:derivace_epsilon} $$

Dosazenm za $\varepsilon(t)$ a $\dot{\varepsilon}(t)$ do pvodn nehomogenn rovnice \eqref{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce} dostaneme vztah

$$ \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} - C(t)\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}\exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} + \frac{E_1}{\eta_1}C(t)\exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t), \tag{30.0} \label{eq:30} $$

ve kterm se oba stejn leny obsahuj $C(t)$ odetou. Dostaneme tedy rovnici

$$ \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t), \tag{31.0} \label{eq:31} $$

kterou upravme na tvar

$$ \dot{C}(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \frac{1}{\exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}}, \tag{32.0} \label{eq:32} $$

a dle jet meme pevst $\exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}$ z jmenovatele do itatele

$$ \dot{C}(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{33.0} \label{eq:33} $$

Integrac obou stran rovnice \eqref{eq:33} obdrme

$$ C(t) = \int{\frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}} \mathrm{d}t. \tag{34.0} \label{eq:34} $$

Po vytknut konstant ped integrl dostaneme

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \int{\exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}} \mathrm{d}t. \tag{35.0} \label{eq:35} $$

Po integraci dostaneme vztah

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 \eta_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \frac{\eta_1}{E_1} \exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} + A, \tag{36.0} \label{eq:C} $$

Kter lze dle zjednoduit

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \hat{\sigma}H(t) \exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} + A, \tag{37.0} \label{eq:C_zjednodusene} $$

kde $A$ je neznm konstanta, kterou lze urit z poten podmnky

$$ \varepsilon(0) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}H(t)}{E_0}. \tag{38.0} \label{eq:pocatecni_podminka} $$

Dosazenm $\varepsilon_h(t)$ z rovnice \eqref{eq:reseni_homo} a $C(t)$ z rovnice \eqref{eq:C_zjednodusene} do vztahu \eqref{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni} zskme

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \left[ \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \exp{\left(\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} \hat{\sigma} H(t) + A \right] \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}, \tag{39.0} \label{eq:39} $$

kterou lze dle upravit

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \hat{\sigma} H(t) + A \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{40.0} \label{eq:40} $$

Z poten podmnky \eqref{eq:pocatecni_podminka} vyplv

$$ \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \hat{\sigma} H(t) + A \exp{\left(0\right)} = \frac{\hat{\sigma}H(t)}{E_0}. \tag{41.0} \label{eq:41} $$

pravami lze vyeit hodnotu konstanty $A$

$$ A = \frac{\hat{\sigma}H(t)}{E_0} - \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \hat{\sigma} H(t), \tag{41.1} $$

$$ A = \frac{\hat{\sigma} H(t) (E_1 - E_0 - E_1)}{E_0 E_1}, \tag{41.2} $$

$$ A = \frac{- \hat{\sigma} H(t) E_0}{E_0 E_1}, \tag{41.3} $$

$$ A = \frac{- \hat{\sigma} H(t)}{E_1}. \tag{41.4} \label{eq:A} $$

Dosazenm do vztahu \eqref{eq:40} dostaneme

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0 E_1} \hat{\sigma} H(t) - \frac{\hat{\sigma} H(t)}{E_1} \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{42.0} $$

Pevedenm na spolenho jmenovatele

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \hat{\sigma} H(t) \frac{E_1 + E_0 - E_0 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}}{E_0 E_1}, \tag{42.1} $$

a pravou dostaneme finln vztah pro pomrnou deformaci Poyting-Thomsonova modelu pi zatovac zkouce

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma} H(t)}{E_0} + \frac{\hat{\sigma} H(t)}{E_1} \left[ 1 - \exp{\left(-\frac{E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} \right]. \tag{42.2} \label{eq:42_2} $$

Zavedenm retardanho asu

$$ \tau_1 = \frac{\eta_1}{E_1}, \tag{43.0} \label{eq:retardacni_cas}$$

dojde ke zjednoduen vztahu \eqref{eq:42_2} na

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - \exp{\left(-\frac{t}{\tau_1}\right)} \right] \right) \hat{\sigma} H(t). \tag{44.0} \label{eq:epsilon_zatezovaci_zkouska} $$

Funkce poddajnosti m tedy tvar

$$ J_0(t) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - \exp{\left(-\frac{t}{\tau_1}\right)} \right] \right) H(t). \tag{45.0} \label{eq:funkce_poddajnosti} $$

In[3]:

E_1 = (40 + 10*b)  # tuhost pruziny 1 (GPa)
ETA_1 = (800 + 100*c) # viskozita tlumice (GPa s)

TAU_1 = ETA_1 / E_1  # retardacni cas (s)
In[4]:
def calculate_J_0(time: int | float | np.ndarray) -> int | float | np.ndarray:
    return (1/E_0 + 1/E_1 * (1 - np.exp(-time/TAU_1))) * calculate_heaviside(time)

def calculate_heaviside(time: int | float | np.ndarray) -> int | float | np.ndarray:
    if isinstance(time, np.ndarray):
        heaviside = np.zeros(time.shape)
        heaviside[time >= 0] = 1
        return heaviside
    else:
        if time >= 0:
            return 1
        else:
            return 0

Odvozen relaxan funkce

Model zatme od asu $t=0\,\mathrm{s}$ konstantnm petvoenm $\varepsilon(t) = \hat\varepsilon H(t)$, kde $H(t)$ je Heavisideova funkce viz \eqref{eq:Heaviside}.

Protoe $\hat\varepsilon H(t)$ je konstantn funkce, pro jej derivaci plat

$$ \hat{\varepsilon} \dot{H}(t) = 0. \tag{46.0} \label{eq:derivace_epsilon_se_striskou} $$

Dosazenm do vztahu \eqref{eq:dif_rce} dostaneme

$$ E_1 \hat{\varepsilon}(t) H(t) = \frac{E_0 + E_1}{E_0} {\sigma}H(t) + \frac{\eta_1}{E_0} \dot{\sigma}(t). \tag {47.0} \label{eq:dif_rce_47} $$

Rovnice \eqref{eq:dif_rce_47} je nehomogenn linern diferenciln rovnice 1. du s konstantnmi koeficienty, postup je stejn jako pi odvozovn funkce poddajnosti $J_0(t).$

Rovnici \eqref{eq:dif_rce_47} pevedeme na tvar

$$ \dot{\sigma}(t) + \frac{E_0 + E_1}{\eta_1} \sigma(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t). \tag {48.0} \label{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce_sigma} $$

een \eqref{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce_sigma} budeme hledat ve tvaru

$$ \sigma(t) = C(t) \sigma_h(t), \tag{49.0} \label{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni_sigma}$$

kde $C(t)$ je hledan funkce promnn $t$ a $\sigma_h(t)$ je een homogenn rovnice

$$ \dot{\sigma}_h(t) + \frac{E_0 + E_1}{\eta_1} \sigma_h(t) = 0. \tag {50.0} \label{eq:homogenni_dif_rce_sigma} $$

Funkci $\sigma_{h}(t)$ budeme hledat ve tvaru

$$ \sigma_{h}(t) = C \exp{(\lambda t)}, \tag{51.0} \label{eq:tvar_reseni_sigma}$$

kde $C$ a $\lambda$ jsou zatm neuren konstanty.

Derivaci rovnice \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_sigma} lze zapsat jako

$$ \dot{\sigma}_{h}(t) = C \lambda \exp{(\lambda t)}. \tag{52.0} \label{eq:tvar_reseni_dsigma}$$

Dosazen vztah \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_sigma} a \eqref{eq:tvar_reseni_dsigma} do \eqref{eq:homogenni_dif_rce_sigma} dostaneme

$$ C \lambda \exp{(\lambda t)} + \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} C \exp{(\lambda t)} = 0. \tag{53.0} \label{eq:dosazeni_homo_rce_sigma} $$

pravou vztahu \eqref{eq:dosazeni_homo_rce_sigma} lze pejt ke tvaru

$$ C \exp{(\lambda t)} \left( \lambda + \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} \right) = 0, \tag{54.0} \label{eq:homo_rce_uprava_sigma}$$

kter je splnn prv tehdy, kdy plat

$$ \lambda + \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} = 0. \tag{55.0} \label{eq:charakteristicka_rovnice_sigma} $$

Z tto charakteristick rovnice lze vypotat konstantu

$$ \lambda = - \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} \tag{56.0} \label{eq:lambda_sigma}. $$

Homogenn een m tedy tvar

$$ \sigma_{h}(t) = C \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}, \tag{57.0} \label{eq:reseni_homo_sigma}$$

Polome $C=C(t)$ a dosadme do rovnice \eqref{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni_sigma}

$$ \sigma(t) = C(t) \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}, \tag{58.0} \label{eq:58}$$

zderivovnm vrazu dostaneme vztah

$$ \dot{\sigma}(t) = \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} - C(t)\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}\exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}. \tag{59.0} \label{eq:derivace_sigma} $$

Dosazenm za $\sigma(t)$ a $\dot{\sigma}(t)$ do pvodn nehomogenn rovnice \eqref{eq:nehomogenni_dif_rce_sigma} dostaneme vztah

$$ \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} - C(t)\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}\exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} + C(t)\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}\exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \tag{60.0} \label{eq:60} $$

ve kterm se oba stejn leny obsahuj $C(t)$ odetou. Dostaneme tedy rovnici

$$ \dot{C}(t) \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t), \tag{61.0} \label{eq:61} $$

kterou upravme na tvar

$$ \dot{C}(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1 \exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t), \tag{62.0} \label{eq:62} $$

a dle jet meme pevst $\exp{\left(- \frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}$ z jmenovatele do itatele

$$ \dot{C}(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t). \tag{63.0} \label{eq:63} $$

Integrac obou stran rovnice \eqref{eq:63} obdrme

$$ C(t) = \int{\frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t)} \mathrm{d}t. \tag{64.0} \label{eq:64} $$

Po vytknut konstant ped integrl dostaneme

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \int{ \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)}} \mathrm{d}t. \tag{65.0} \label{eq:65} $$

Po integraci dostaneme vztah

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{\eta_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \frac{\eta_1}{E_0+E_1} \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} + A, \tag{66.0} \label{eq:C_sigma} $$

kter lze dle zjednoduit

$$ C(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} + A, \tag{67.0} \label{eq:C_sigma_zjednodusene} $$

kde $A$ je neznm konstanta, kterou lze urit z poten podmnky

$$ \sigma(0) = E_0 \hat{\varepsilon}H(t). \tag{68.0} \label{eq:pocatecni_podminka_sigma} $$

Dosazenm $\sigma_h(t)$ z rovnice \eqref{eq:reseni_homo_sigma} a $C(t)$ z rovnice \eqref{eq:C_sigma_zjednodusene} do vztahu \eqref{eq:predpokladany_tvar_reseni_sigma} zskme

$$ \sigma(t) = \left[ \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \exp{\left(\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} t \right)} + A \right] \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}, \tag{69.0} \label{eq:69} $$

kterou lze dle upravit

$$ \sigma(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) + A \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{70.0} \label{eq:70} $$

Z poten podmnky \eqref{eq:pocatecni_podminka_sigma} vyplv

$$ E_0 \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) + A \exp{\left(0\right)}. \tag{81.0} \label{eq:81} $$

pravami lze vyeit hodnotu konstanty $A$

$$ A = E_0 \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) - \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t), \tag{71.1} $$

$$ A = \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \left( E_0 - \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \right), \tag{71.2} $$

Dosazenm do vztahu \eqref{eq:70} dostaneme

$$ \sigma(t) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) + \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \left( E_0 - \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0+E_1} \right) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)}. \tag{72.0} $$

Pevedenm na spolenho jmenovatele dostaneme

$$ \sigma(t) = \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \left( \frac{ E_0 E_1 + E_0 (E_0 + E_1) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} - E_0 E_1 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} }{E_0 + E_1} \right). \tag{72.1} $$

Dle lze vytknout ped zvorku $\frac{E_0}{E_0+E_1}$

$$ \sigma(t) = \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + (E_0 + E_1) \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} - E_1 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} \right). \tag{72.2} $$

Setenm vraz v zvorce dostaneme finln vztah pro napt Poyting-Thomsonova modelu pi deforman zkouce

$$ \sigma(t) = \hat{\varepsilon}H(t) \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + E_0 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} \right). \tag{72.3} \label{eq:72_3} $$

Relaxan funkce m tedy tvar

$$ R_0(t) = H(t) \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + E_0 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1}t\right)} \right). \tag{73.0} \label{eq:relaxacni_funkce} $$

Z grafu je patrn, e vztah

$$ R_0(t) = \frac{1}{J_0(t)} \tag{74.0} \label{eq:R_is_J} $$

plat pouze pro $t = 0 \, \mathrm{s}$ a pro $t \rightarrow +\infty$.

Ovme dosazenm pro $t = 0 \, \mathrm{s}$ do vztahu \eqref{eq:funkce_poddajnosti}

$$ J_0(0) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - \exp{\left(-\frac{0}{\tau_1}\right)} \right] \right) H(0) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - \exp{0} \right] \right) \cdot 1 = \frac{1}{E_0}, \tag{75.0} \label{eq:J0_0} $$

a do \eqref{eq:relaxacni_funkce}

$$ R_0(0) = H(0) \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + E_0 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} \cdot 0 \right)} \right) = 1 \cdot \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + E_0 \exp{(0)} \right) = \frac{E_0(E_0 + E_1)}{E_0 + E_1} = E_0. \tag{76.0} \label{eq:R0_0} $$

To sam provedeme pro $t \rightarrow +\infty$.

$$ J_0(t \rightarrow +\infty) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - \exp{\left(-\frac{t \rightarrow +\infty}{\tau_1}\right)} \right] \right) H(t \rightarrow +\infty) = \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[1 - 0 \right] \right) \cdot 1 = \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} = \frac{E_0+E_1}{E_0 E_1}, \tag{77.0} \label{eq:J0_oo} $$

$$ R_0(t \rightarrow +\infty) = H(t \rightarrow +\infty) \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1 + E_0 \exp{\left(-\frac{E_0+E_1}{\eta_1} \cdot t \rightarrow +\infty \right)} \right) = 1 \cdot \frac{E_0}{E_0 + E_1} \left( E_1\right) = \frac{E_0 E_1}{E_0 + E_1}. \tag{78.0} \label{eq:R0_oo} $$

Z vsledk je zejm, e vztah \eqref{eq:R_is_J} plat pro $t = 0 \, \mathrm{s}$ a pro $t \rightarrow +\infty$.

Popis vvoje deformace pi linern rostoucm napt

Pedpokldejme linern rst napt z nulov hodnoty v ase $t_0 = 0 \, \mathrm{s}$ a do hodnoty $\sigma(t_1) = \hat{\sigma}$.

Funkci napt lze tedy vyjdit vztahem

$$ \sigma(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1}t, \tag{79.0} $$

a jej derivaci

$$ \dot{\sigma}(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1}. \tag{80.0} $$

V tomto ppad se pomrn deformace vypot podle vztahu

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \int_{t_0}^t J(t, t') \dot{\sigma}(t') \mathrm{d}t \tag{81.0} \label{eq:pomerna_deformace} $$

Dosazenm za $J(t,t')$ a $\dot{\sigma}(t)$ dostaneme rovnici

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \int_0^t \left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \left[ 1 - \exp \left( -\frac{t-t'}{\tau_1} \right) \right] \right) \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1} \mathrm{d}t'. \tag{81.0} $$

Rozdlenm na dl integrly a vytknutm konstant ped integrl dostaneme

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1} \left[ \frac{1}{E_0} \int_0^t \mathrm{d}t' + \frac{1}{E_1} \int_0^t \mathrm{d}t' - \frac{1}{E_0} \int_0^t \exp \left( -\frac{t-t'}{\tau_1} \right) \mathrm{d}t' \right]. \tag{81.1} $$

Integrac zskme

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1} \left[ \frac{1}{E_0} [t']_0^t + \frac{1}{E_1} [t']_0^t - \frac{1}{E_1} \tau_1 \exp \left( -\frac{t}{\tau_1} \right) \left[ \exp{ \left( \frac{t'}{\tau_1} \right) - 1} \right]_0^t \right]. \tag{81.2} $$

Dosazenm dostaneme vraz pro pomrnou deformaci

$$ \varepsilon(t) = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{t_1} \left[ \frac{t}{E_0} + \frac{t}{E_1} - \frac{\tau_1}{E_1} + \frac{\tau_1}{E_1} \exp{\left( \frac{-t}{\tau_1} \right)} \right]. \tag{81.3} $$

Pi extrmn rychlm zaten ($t \rightarrow 0^+)$ se deformuje pouze pruina, vztah pro deformaci tedy lze napsat jako

$$ \varepsilon = \frac{\hat{\sigma}}{E_0}. \tag{82.0} $$

Pi extrmn rychlm zaten ($t \rightarrow \infty)$ se rychlost deformace tlumie bl nule ($\dot{\varepsilon}_v \rightarrow 0$) a model se chov jako dv pruiny zapojen sriov, lze tedy pst

$$ \varepsilon = \hat{\sigma}\left( \frac{1}{E_0} + \frac{1}{E_1} \right). \tag{83.0} $$

SIGMA_HAT = 8  # (GPa)
def stress(t: int| float | np.ndarray, t_1: int | float) -> int | float | np.ndarray:
    return (SIGMA_HAT / t_1) * t

def strain(t: int | float | np.ndarray, t_1: int | float) -> int | float | np.ndarray:
    return (SIGMA_HAT / t_1) * (t/E_0 + t/E_1 - TAU_1/E_1 + TAU_1/E_1 * np.exp(-t/TAU_1))
